page.title: 13AINSDALE NATURE RESERVE 2.
page.content: THE MOBILE AND THE FIXED DUNES ARE FAIRLY SIMILAR ALTHOUGH MOST OF THE PLANT LIFE ON THE MOBILE DUNES IS MARAM GRASS WHEREAS THE FIXED DUNES MAINLY HAVE RED FESCUE.ALTHOUGH THERE ARE A FEW FLOWERS SUCH AS BIRDS-FOOT TREFOIL,EVENING PRIMROSE,RAGWORT AND DUNE HELLEBORINE WHICH IS A VERY RARE ORCHID.THESE PLANTS ARE ONE OF THE FIRST LINKS IN A LARGE FOOD CHAIN.NEXT ARE THE INSECTS SUCH AS FROG HOPPERS,APHIDS AND A LARGE RANGE OF DIFFERENT BUGS.THESE IN TURN ARE EATEN BY SPIDERS,LADYBIRDS,LACE-WINGS AND TIGER BEETLES.THESE AGAIN ARE EATEN BY LARGER ANIMALS LIKE BIRDS,RABBITS,HEDGE-HOGS,SQUIRELS AND BATS.LAST OF ALL IN THE FOOD CHAIN COME THE LARGER ANIMALS LIKE FOXES AND SMALL BIRDS OF PREY.
